column1: How easy was it to locate the course registration or login option on the Swayam home page?
column2: How clearly was the login page layout organized and understandable?
column3: How easy was it to choose and use your preferred login method (e.g., Google, Microsoft, etc.)?
column4: How confident were you that your login was successful after clicking “Sign In”?
column5: How easy was it to navigate from the login page to your profile or course dashboard?
column6: How easy was it to find and understand your enrolled or available courses on the profile page?
column7: How easy was it to locate the course or assignment link on the Swayam platform?
column8: How intuitive was the left hand navigation panel for finding the weekly assignments?
column9: How quickly were you able to identify the correct 'Week Assignment' link on the course page?
column10: How clear was the layout of the Assignment/Quiz page once it opened?
column11: How comfortable did you feel navigating between questions and the submit button on the assignment page?
column12: How consistent did you find the interface design across all pages?
column13: How well did the system guide you step-by-step from login to assignment completion?
column14: How easy it was to locate and access the “My Courses” section from the main NPTEL entry page?
column15: The “My Courses” page displayed my enrolled courses clearly and made it simple to open one.
column16: I was able to quickly identify and select the correct course video (e.g., Week lecture) from the course page.
column17: The left navigation panel (Week/Module list) on the course page was intuitive to use.
column18: The video playback page layout (player, transcript, Q&A) was visually clear and easy to understand.
column19: I could easily control video playback actions (play, pause, seek, full screen) without confusion.
column20: The transition from course page to video playback felt smooth and consistent in design.
column21: I was able to focus on the video content without distraction from other elements on the page.
column22: It was easy to locate the “Explore Courses” option on the entry page.
column23: The course listing layout helped me quickly scan and compare multiple courses.
column24: The filter and search tools on the course list were clear and easy to use.
column25: I could identify the most relevant course titles without much effort.
column26: The transition from the list to the course-details page felt smooth and intuitive.
column27: The course-details page presented essential information (overview, syllabus, instructor) in an organized way.
column28: I could easily locate the “Enroll” or “Start Learning” button on the details page.
column29: The platform allowed me to explore courses efficiently without confusion or distraction.
column30: Overall how good was the platform?
